Jan 30 2009 	New home in Beijing	Frequent visitor to Beijing ( six trips in 5 months), and I've now found my preferred hotel. Rooms are very good size, excellent bathrooms and the bed with selection of pillows is extremely comfortable. Most all the staff have good or very good English. Of particular note is the dining / breakfast room. I had perhaps one of the best simple fish/vegetables dishes ever. The Chinese food is also very good. Pool and gym facilities are first class and I even tried a basic massage in the spa - very good if a little pricey. Next return trip is February and I have no need to look anywhere else.	
Jan 1 2009 	A Truly Grand Hotel	This being our first time in Beijing, we had anticipated walking quite a bit touring the attractions and decided that it would be nice to come back to a nice comfortable hotel after a long day of sightseeing and shopping. On a tip from our travel agent we chose this hotel. The hotel is located in the Central Business District and about a 25 minute taxi ride from the airport. We stayed 4 days and 3 nights at this hotel and it was a wonderful experience. The decor of the lobby was modern and classy, and the staff were very helpful and accommodating right from the start. The rooms are well decorated with a flat screen tv, free internet connection, and a huge bathroom. The tub was large and ideal for soaking in a bubble bath at the end of the day. The separate shower had good space and dual shower heads. Also, the room was well stocked with some bathroom toiletries. Everything about the room was quite new and there were no signs of wear and tear at all. There was even a complimentary shoe polish service. Perhaps the one thing I would suggest would be for the hotel to get firmer mattresses for the beds and firmer pillows as well. The breakfast buffet was quite good compared to other hotel buffets that we have had with a good mixture of Asian and Western breakfast food. Perhaps because we were there in December but the breakfast dining room was never full. In fact there was one time when our party were the only guests dining in the room. The hotel is a business hotel however, we saw several families with young children there and it seems that the hotel caters well to a diverse clientèle. The exercise room is big with a juice bar, and several exercise machines. One thing that we regret was that the swimming pool was not opened due to construction. The pool's size was tremendous and it had to be one of the biggest indoor pools that I have seen in a hotel. We would certainly stay at this hotel again in future trips to Beijing if not only to be able to swim in the pool! Besides that, it boasts a good location where you can get practically anywhere by taxi or subway, and is in an area that is less touristy than other areas.	
Nov 18 2008 	Nice place to stay	This hotel locates outside the inner city (inner city is where the Forbidden Palace is located.), around the second ring road. However, there is a subway near by that you can take and is faster than using taxi because of heavy traffic in Beijing. But beware of high volume of bodies using the subway. There are about 16 million people living in Beijing, therefore, it can be tiring trying to fight and push your way through the train door. Since the hotel is quite new, I can smell the new paint and at times make me feel sick. The room itself is modern and very nice. Flat TV screen, free internet connection, nice bed and pillows, coffee/tea/Chinese tea are plus addition. The shower is fantastic with two shower heads jetting nice warm water. The staff is friendly and helpful. Buffet breakfast and lunch are very good with varieties of Asian and Western choices. The hotel has a nice gym and a nice-looking swimming pool. Unfortunately, the pool was not ready to use during my visit.This is a nice place to stay and I can find silence and peace after wondering through a mass of people during my sight-seeing.	
