Nov 13 2008	A great experience	This is a new hotel only having opened just prior to the Olympics.The staff were fabulous, polite and very willing to help and accommodate your requests.It is located within a 1 minute walk from the subway station which is part of the new line for the Olympics. The subway enables you to travel around Beijing relatively easily and cheaply.The rooms are modern, comfortable and clean.The executive lounge is pleasant and staffed by a great team of people.The hotel has a good gym and a huge indoor swimming pool. The restaurants are good, although sometimes on occasions some of the buffet food was a little dry, but the variety is good.The bar has a jazz band which can be a little noisy and overwhelming in the evenings, but is still worth a visit.Overall this is an extremely good hotel and one worth staying at as a base for a trip to and around Beijing.	
